      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm, mix, rest",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm the {{honey}}, {{dark-brown-sugar}} and {{unsalted-butter}} together in a saucepan over a low heat until smooth and just thinned. Cool for 5 minutes. Mix the {{plain-flour}}, {{almond-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{cloves}} and {{mixed-peel}} in a wide bowl. Pour in the warm honey mix and add the beaten {{eggs}}. Stir to a soft, sticky dough. Wrap and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "rest in the fridge for at least 12 hours",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99bpxp000028v423nudtfr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", up to 3 days.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, cut, bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan and line two baking trays. Roll the rested dough on a lightly floured surface to about 8 mm thick. Cut 24 biscuits with a 6 mm round cutter. Set on the trays with 3 cm between each. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes; the biscuits should puff slightly, the tops should look set and matte, and the colour should be a deep tan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze warm, store",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "While the biscuits bake, whisk the {{icing-sugar}} with the {{water}} to a thin pourable glaze. As soon as the biscuits come out, brush the tops with the glaze; it dries to a fine matte shell as the biscuits cool. Store in an airtight tin; the flavour improves over the first 3 days.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
